T(n)= 3T(n-1)+1
T(0)=2
T(n) = 3T(n-1)+1 = 9T(n-2) + 3 + 1 = 27T(n-3) + 9 + 3 + 1 = ...
T(n) = \sum_{m=0}^{n-1} 3^m + 2\cdot3^n = \frac{5\cdot 3^n-1}{2}
T(1) = 3T(0) + 1 = 3.2 + 1 = 7
T(2) = 3T(1) + 1 = 3.7 + 1 = 3(3.2 + 1) + 1 = 9.2 + 3 + 1 = 22
T(3) = 3T(2) + 1 = 3.22 + 1 = 3(3(3.2 + 1)+1)+1 = 27.2 + 9 + 3 + 1 = 67
T(n) = 2.3^n + 3^{n-1} + \cdots + 1
